replies.bodyText: I'm fine with the 'a,b,c,d' correction, thank you. These extra spaces are the result of VS Code's formatting and while it seems to have gotten better the if/else begin/end braces still sometimes end up with an extra space at the end.
replies.author: JimSuplizio

replies.bodyText:
@JimSuplizio ,
Thank you for your response. 🙇

These extra spaces are the result of VS Code's formatting

We  can configure VS Code to remove trailing space: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/30884131/remove-trailing-spaces-automatically-or-with-a-shortcut
replies.author: chenrujun

replies.bodyText: @chenrujun thanks for pointing that out. I'll get "files.trimTrailingWhitespace": true added to my local config.
replies.author: JimSuplizio
